Acknowledgements & context

This project originated as a continuation of a group case study
("Kabamo") for the module Supply Chain Management in Health Care
(SCMHC), MBA International Health, Swiss TPH. The country "Kabamo" is
fictional. The sleeping-space / mattress enumeration approach that
informs the demand register follows published field method (the
"Senegal approach").

The accompanying USSD demonstrator is a prototype. It is NOT a
production system. Any real deployment that collects household data
requires an appropriate legal basis, a named data controller/custodian,
informed consent, and purpose limitation under the applicable data
protection law (e.g. Tanzania PDPA 2022, GDPR-derived obligations).
